{"id":1927,"date":"2016-05-11T06:29:44","date_gmt":"2016-05-11T03:29:44","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/?p=1927"},"modified":"2016-05-11T06:33:40","modified_gmt":"2016-05-11T03:33:40","slug":"ramadan-2016-fundraising","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/ramadan-2016-fundraising\/","title":{"rendered":"Ramadan 2016 &#8211; Fundraising"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/IMAG0891.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-1771\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/IMAG0891-300x170.jpg\" alt=\"IMAG0891\" width=\"321\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/IMAG0891-300x170.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/IMAG0891.jpg 941w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 321px) 100vw, 321px\" \/><\/a>QWT will be fundraising from May 11 to May 30 2016, for its annual Ramadan food distribution project. This year we will be\u00a0targeting to feed 1,000 poor Zakat eligible families across Pakistan. The cost of feeding an average family of 5 members will be $55 (KD 16; Rs 5,500). Each family will be provided with approximately 50kg of un-cooked food stables including flour, rice, sugar, lentils, chickpeas,\u00a0cooking\u00a0oil, ghee, gram flour, dates, tea and mix spices.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">QWT has been organizing Ramadan food distributions for the past eight years. Last year we distributed 71.25 tons of food, to 1,350 families (<a title=\"Ramadan 2013 \" href=\"http:\/\/10.0.0.56\/?p=1776\" target=\"_blank\">details<\/a>).<\/p>\n<h2>Project Summary<\/h2>\n<p><strong>Fundraising Period:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>May 11 to May 30 2016<\/p>\n<p><strong>Beneficiaries:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>1,000 families (approximately 5,000 people).<\/p>\n<p><strong>Project Execution:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Food will be distributed between June 1-4 in collaboration with various partner organizations like Muslim Aid, and Almustafa Development Network. The beneficiaries will be\u00a0pre-screened prior to the distribution and all efforts will be made to ensure they are Zakat eligible.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Why Pakistan:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Poverty is widespread in Pakistan and is particularly predominant in rural areas. Nearly two thirds of the population, and 80 per cent of the country\u2019s poor people, live in rural parts of the country. Studies on poverty show that every third Pakistani is living his life below the poverty line. About 58.7 million out of 180 million Pakistanis are living below the poverty line.<a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/11\/DSC02156-e1432883984994.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1415\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/11\/DSC02156-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Village Thor Chhaho\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/11\/DSC02156-e1432883984994.jpg\"><br \/>\n<\/a>According to the Human Development Index, 60.3% of Pakistan&#8217;s population lives on under $2 a day, and some 22.6% live under $1 a day. Wealth distribution in Pakistan is highly uneven, with the top 10% of the population earning 27.6% and the bottom 10% earning only 4.1% of the income. According to the United Nations Human Development Report, Pakistan&#8217;s human development indicators, especially those for women, fall significantly below those of countries with comparable levels of per-capita income.<\/p>\n<h2>Donate Online<\/h2>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1080\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1080\" style=\"width: 170px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a title=\"Ramadan Food Distribution\" href=\"https:\/\/uk.virginmoneygiving.com\/fundraiser-web\/donate\/makeDonationForFundraiserDisplay.action?fundraiserActivityId=443249\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-1080\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/478678683c.jpg\" alt=\"Ramadan Food Distribution\" width=\"170\" height=\"125\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1080\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Ramadan Food Distribution<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Online donations will be made in British Pounds, and \u00a31.00 = $1.44, and \u00a31.00 = KD 0.440.<\/p>\n<h2>Donate via bank wire transfer<\/h2>\n<h3><strong>Pakistan<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><strong>Account Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Qidwai Welfare Trust<\/p>\n<p><strong>Account Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a00055001586000087<\/p>\n<p><strong>IBAN Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0PK93BURJ0055001586000087<\/p>\n<p><strong>Bank Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Burj Bank Ltd.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Address &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0F8 Markaz Branch, Islamabad, Pakistan<\/p>\n<p><strong>Swift Code &#8211;\u00a0<\/strong>BURJPKKAXXX<\/p>\n<p><strong>Currency &#8211;\u00a0<\/strong>Pakistani Rupee<\/p>\n<h3>.<\/h3>\n<h3><strong>United Kingdom\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><strong>Account Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0The Charity Network<\/p>\n<p><strong>Account Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a021050953<\/p>\n<p><strong>IBAN Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0GB77NWBK54210721050953<\/p>\n<p><strong>Bank Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Natwest Bank<\/p>\n<p><strong>Address &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Basford Branch, 536 Valley Road, Nottingham\u00a0NG5 1JJ, UK<\/p>\n<p><strong>Swift Code &#8211;\u00a0<\/strong>NWBKGB2L<\/p>\n<p><strong>Currency &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0British Pound<\/p>\n<p><em><strong>Please, drop us an email at\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:donation@qidwaiwelfare.com\">donation@qidwaiwelfare.com<\/a>\u00a0after you have made the donation, so we can followup with the bank.<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>QWT will be fundraising 